Between 2018 and 2023, the number of lecturers increased by 17.2 percent

In 2018, the number of lecturers was 337. By 2023, this had increased by 58, bringing the total to 395. The number of associate professors and assistant professors also grew, with a 12.2 percent increase (25 more associate professors) and a 3.9 percent increase (8 more assistant professors), respectively. In contrast, the number of full professors decreased by 2.4 percent, representing a decline of 19 professors since 2018.
